UML:TaggedValue.value: Common gazetteer model, defining the properties captured by SIRF for spatial object identifiers. Based on ISO 19112 semantics, with added metadata to support provenance of identifiers in a federated environment.
Metadata carrier and access point for sets of gazetteer entries. Gazetteers are hierarchical
Country of application to support faceted search
Name of gazetteer, to be displayed in selection lists etc
Count of entries at last harvest.
URI identifier for the object once registered. This is the citable reference for the object for external applications.
Reference to licence under which source dataset is accessible.
Code to assist in selecting official names if required.
Allows a gazetteer to belong to one or more collections - virtual gazetteers using a subregister pattern
A URI can be attached to specific metadata about the content it references by modelling the content. - in which case use the specific codeList rather than the generic LID_URI datatype.

This is a simplified demo version of a gazetteer entry. It ignores feature type classification, preferred language and source feature type aspects. This model will be replaced by a formal profile of ISO 19112 in an operational context.
URI of country entity (i.e. ref to UNGEGN gazetteer)
Description (typically provided by original source dataset)

URI identifier for the object once registered. This is the citable reference for the object for external applications. Typically it will be the constructed via the sourceID extending the containing Gazetteer URI identifier.
Vocabulary URI. This URI will be provided by the vocabulary server. (This will be implemented in the next phase)
Registration status - URIs will be stable, so need to be resolved even if record has been removed, or identified as a duplicate.
Identifier defined by original source dataset This is the ID used in the WFS service to identify each gazetteer data entry.
A full URL which can be used to query original WFS service for this particular gazetteer entry.

Source Location Type vocabulary term as a URI identifier using Linked Data principles. This URI will be point to definitions using provided by the vocabulary server. ( It will be implemented in the next phase)
This dependency was generated by Solid Ground - ModelMapping function
Unknown - the actual status cannot be determined
UNGEGN best practice for gazetteer classification.
A virtual gazetteer aggregating other gazetteers for a specific purpose.
Other data set containing a set of spatial feature identifiers and names.
Data set maintained by a designated jurisdictional naming authority.
Data set made available through SDI infrastructure
URL - could point to any form of resource.
Many-to-many collection pattern. Gazetteers should contain either subRegisters or gazetteerEntries
A identification code for a place, typically not using a natural language.
A name used by inhabitants of a place in a recognised official language of the place.,
A place name used by foreigners instead of the native-language version used by its inhabitants
It is not known whether a name is an endonym or exonym, for example because the language has not been positively identified.

This CodeList indicates that a set of feature codes is to be managed, and allows the information model for these types to be referenced. The controlled vocabulary will contain items matching the type model
A HTTP URI in the form of a URL that can be resolved to multiple forms of resource according to the LID specification
